  "title": "Приоритизировать diagnostics manual API profile в `update api-manifest`",
  "description": "## T-0992 [ ] P3: Приоритизировать diagnostics manual API profile в `update api-manifest`\n\n- Создана: 2026-07-08T18:11:00+03:00\n- Состояние: open\n- Приоритет: P3\n- Execution class: `internal-substrate`\n- Scheduling tier: `later`\n- Зависимости: T-0990\n- Ссылки:\n  - Доменный документ: `docs/documentation/api-manifest.md`\n  - Исходный код: `eng/Electron2D.Build/RepositoryPolicyVerifiers.cs`\n  - Тесты: `tests/Electron2D.Tests.Integration/RepositoryBuildToolTests.cs`\n  - Источник follow-up: `docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r05.md`\n\n### Execution contract\n\n- Task type: tooling-diagnostics-hardening\n- Ready-to-start:\n  - task state is `open`.\n  - manual API profile contract remains owned by `T-0990`.\n  - a focused RED test can create an invalid manual profile while runtime still exports public types.\n- Stop conditions:\n  - the change would approve or reject public API types instead of improving diagnostics.\n  - the change would weaken fail-fast behavior for exported public types missing `approved`.\n- May change:\n  - `update api-manifest --check` diagnostic ordering/aggregation and direct tests/docs.\n  - generated local documentation index if docs are updated.\n  - task notes and diary for this task.\n- Must not change:\n  - runtime public API implementation.\n  - owner approval decisions in `data/api/electron2d-public-api-profile.json`.\n  - saved audit reports.\n- Required outputs:\n  - invalid manual profile diagnostics are printed before or alongside unapproved export diagnostics in `update api-manifest --check`.\n  - focused regression covering invalid profile plus exported runtime public type.\n- Required commands:\n  - focused `update api-manifest --check` diagnostic regression.\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build -- verify audit-followups`\n  - `git diff --check`\n- External audit:\n  - not required unless bundled with a parent API tooling package.\n\n### Самодостаточное описание\n\nr05 primary audit for `T-0990` found a diagnostic debt: `update api-manifest --check` can read and accumulate manual profile validation errors, but the exported-type gate may return `E2D-BUILD-API-PROFILE-UNAPPROVED-EXPORT` first when runtime exports public types. `verify api-compatibility` already prints profile validation errors, and required empty-profile fail-fast behavior is proven; this task improves diagnostic completeness for `update api-manifest`.\n\n### Internal substrate acceptance contract\n\n- Profile shape/decision diagnostics stay visible even when exported runtime public types are unapproved.\n- The command remains fail-closed.\n- The fix is diagnostic-only and does not change public API inclusion decisions.\n\n### Критерии приёмки\n\n- [ ] Focused test covers invalid profile plus exported runtime public type.\n- [ ] `update api-manifest --check` reports the relevant `E2D-BUILD-API-PROFILE-*` validation diagnostic.\n- [ ] Existing empty-profile fail-fast diagnostics remain intact.\n\n### Подзадачи\n\n- [ ] Add RED regression for invalid manual profile diagnostics in `update api-manifest --check`.\n- [ ] Adjust diagnostic ordering/aggregation in build-tool profile checks.\n- [ ] Update docs if command diagnostics contract changes.\n- [ ] Run focused checks, `verify audit-followups` and `git diff --check`.\n\n### Current evidence\n\n- audit-followup-closure:\n  - source: docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r01.md\n  - id: FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F2\n  - state: tracked-new\n  - target: T-0992\n  - rationale: Primary audit r01 classified hidden invalid-profile diagnostics in `update api-manifest --check` as P3 diagnostics hardening. Current `T-0990` fail-closed behavior is proven, so this task tracks diagnostic completeness separately.\n- audit-followup-closure:\n  - source: docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r02.md\n  - id: FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F2\n  - state: tracked-new\n  - target: T-0992\n  - rationale: Primary audit r02 repeated the same `update api-manifest --check` diagnostics finding. `T-0992` owns diagnostic completeness across all `T-0990` iterations.\n- audit-followup-closure:\n  - source: docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r03.md\n  - id: FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F2\n  - state: tracked-new\n  - target: T-0992\n  - rationale: Primary audit r03 repeated the same `update api-manifest --check` diagnostics finding. `T-0992` owns diagnostic completeness across all `T-0990` iterations.\n- audit-followup-closure:\n  - source: docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r04.md\n  - id: FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F2\n  - state: tracked-new\n  - target: T-0992\n  - rationale: Primary audit r04 repeated the same `update api-manifest --check` diagnostics finding. `T-0992` owns diagnostic completeness across all `T-0990` iterations.\n- audit-followup-closure:\n  - source: docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r05.md\n  - id: FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F2\n  - state: tracked-new\n  - target: T-0992\n  - rationale: Primary audit r05 classified hidden invalid-profile diagnostics in `update api-manifest --check` as P3 diagnostics hardening. Current `T-0990` fail-closed behavior is proven, so this task tracks diagnostic completeness separately.\n- audit-followup-closure:\n  - source: docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r06.md\n  - id: FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F2\n  - state: tracked-existing\n  - target: T-0992\n  - rationale: Primary audit r06 repeated the same `update api-manifest --check` diagnostics finding and explicitly pointed to existing `T-0992`; no new task is needed.\n- audit-followup-closure:\n  - source: docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r07.md\n  - id: FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F2\n  - state: tracked-existing\n  - target: T-0992\n  - rationale: Accepted primary audit r07 repeated the same `update api-manifest --check` diagnostics finding and explicitly pointed to existing `T-0992`; no new task is needed.\n- audit-followup-closure:\n  - source: docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r08.md\n  - id: FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F2\n  - state: tracked-existing\n  - target: T-0992\n  - rationale: Primary audit r08 repeated the same `update api-manifest --check` diagnostics finding and explicitly pointed to existing `T-0992`; no new task is needed.\n- audit-followup-closure:\n  - source: docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r09.md\n  - id: FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F2\n  - state: tracked-existing\n  - target: T-0992\n  - rationale: Accepted primary audit r09 repeated the same `update api-manifest --check` diagnostics finding and explicitly pointed to existing `T-0992`; no new task is needed.\n- audit-followup-closure:\n  - source: docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r10.md\n  - id: FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F2\n  - state: tracked-existing\n  - target: T-0992\n  - rationale: Accepted primary audit r10 repeated the same `update api-manifest --check` diagnostics finding and explicitly pointed to existing `T-0992`; no new task is needed.\n\n### Заметки агента\n\n2026-07-08T18:11:00+03:00 - Создано как `tracked-new` closure для `FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F2` из `docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r05.md`; finding перенесён в P3 API manifest diagnostics hardening.\n\n",
